The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Gayle defends delay
                                                   Gayle defends delay
                      
	London: Chris Gayle has defended his decision to spend only two days in England with two practice sessions before leading the West Indies in the first cricket Test at Lords on Wednesday. Gayle delayed his arrival until Monday morning as he was engaged playing in the Indian Premier League (IPL) in South Africa.         
	He told a news conference at Lords on Tuesday that he had been given permission by the West Indies Cricket Board to delay his arrival and had played big matches soon after long flights in the past.         
	Im fresh, he said. Im ready to go, I got in early in the morning and had a net session in the afternoon.           (REUTERS)                                                                                                                   
